negative.review:
Got mixed feelings about this demo. On the one hand,
+ the authors' intent is clear and well-intended: they gathered best parts of different HoMM games and mixed them into one, with the prevailing amount of ideas taken from the third, most popular game. There is branching of unit evolutions from the 4th, hero support on the battlefield from the 5th, but the majority of Olden Era strongly resembles the third instalment. These elements seem to work well together;
+ there are also new factions, which is always exciting, especially the Schism. Who doesn't want to reminisce about good old days of In the Wake of Gods;
+ there is a couple of new peculiar mechanics, for example, faction laws, that can enhance your playthroughs and make them more unique, and a new game mode, Arena;
+ the demo itself is very solid, there are few bugs;
+ creature and town designs put a new spin on the old visuals.

However, there are points I can't ignore:
 - as I was playing it I couldn't help but think: if so much has been borrowed from the third game, what's the point of making Olden Era at all? Sure, there are a few new ideas as well as additions from other instalments, but from what I've seen so far, this game is about 85% Heroes of Might and Magic 3, down to the sound effects! I guess taking any other road would most likely lead to a failure: make a unique game distinct from previous instalments, and fans will eat you alive; make more of the same and become the FIFA of turn-based strategies. HoMM 3 surely is a timeless masterpiece but, alas, you can't earn on it again;
- which brings up another point: I find the design direction chosen for this game to be very... Warcrafty? Mobile game-like? It's really cartoony and doesn't help set the game apart from any other mobile fantasy game. There is nostalgia for old RPGs at the moment, so Unfrozen could capitalise on it by just polishing up the HoMM 3 graphics (since it's halfway there anyway) instead of giving it a completely forgettable look;
 - not a single music track left an impression on me;
 - the UI in this game is abysmal. I'm no connoisseur but I misclicked on things on multiple occasions, had to guess functions of a few unlabelled or tiny buttons, spent some time looking for the hero and castle icons (!) when I just started playing. The interface elements are too spread out, and (this is hopefully just a demo nitpick and it will be changed later on) their design is often bare-bone;
- I had trouble interacting with objects on the map, since you need to click on the specific part of it to interact, as well as with units on the battlefield if they stand in a tight vertical formation, there is simply not enough vertical space for them. Also, a lot of pickups on the map are obscured by other map objects;
- the randomly generated maps seem to love the treasure troves, there are simply too many of them;
- what is the point of alchemical dust? In my playthroughs its only role was to hinder my progress;
- why does the vampire unit from Necropolis look so much like Hordak from She-Ra and the Princesses of Power??

Overall, at the moment I'm not too sure about Olden Era, and in my eyes it loses in comparison with the game it is trying to imitate, Heroes of Might and Magic 3. But that's one of the purposes of a demo, to gauge audience's reaction and report on progress. Good luck Unfrozen!
